        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 7:35PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 735 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Vestavia Hills, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pinson, Mountain Brook, Chalkville, Shops of Grand River, Five Points
South, Liberty Park, Vandiver, Vestavia Hills, Camp Winnataska,
U.A.B. Campus, Highland Park Golf Course, Clay, Inverness, Grants
Mill Road Bridge, Cahaba Heights, Leeds, Chula Vista, Birmingham Race
Course, Ruffner Mountain, and Trussville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
